---

<CoursePageLayout
  title={meta.title}
  description={meta.description}
  canonical={meta.canonical}
  lastUpdated={meta.lastUpdated}
  noIndex={true}
  pageHeading="Owner Builder Course QLD — Online Training for Your Permit"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { label: 'Owner Builder Training', href: '/owner-builder' },
    { label: 'QLD Owner Builder' },
  ]}
  courseName="QLD Owner Builder Course"
  provider={{ name: 'ABE Education', url: 'https://www.abeeducation.edu.au' }}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <AnswerCapsuleSection
    heading="What is an owner builder course and who needs one in QLD?"
    answer="An owner builder course prepares you to manage building work on your own property in Queensland. Most people must complete an approved owner builder course before they apply to QBCC for an owner builder permit, and you need that permit for residential building work valued at more than $11,000."
    body="Owner building means running a residential project on your own land without a licensed builder overseeing it. You take on the head contractor role: engaging trades, scheduling work, and making sure the build meets the National Construction Code. The course gives you the knowledge to do that safely and lawfully before you apply for your permit. It is the same starting point whether you are building a new home or taking on a major renovation."
  >
    <BodyParagraph text="Do I always need the course? Most applicants do. You are exempt if you hold a current QBCC licence, in which case you enter your licence number on the permit form, or if you hold certain qualifications or an interstate builder or trade contractor's licence. Building experience on its own, without a formal qualification, is not enough for an exemption." />
    <SourceCitation>
      <a href={QBCC_COURSES} class="link-dotted" rel="external">QBCC</a>
    </SourceCitation>
    <VerificationNote lastVerified="2026-05-22">
      <a href={QBCC_ABOUT} class="link-dotted" rel="external">QBCC</a>
    </VerificationNote>
    <CrossRefLink href="/owner-builder" label="View all owner builder course states" />
  </AnswerCapsuleSection>

  <NumberedStepsSection
    heading="How does the owner builder course work?"
    answer="Enrol online and work through the modules at your own pace, then complete the assessment to receive your Certificate of Completion. You take that certificate to QBCC when you apply for your owner builder permit. The course is fully online, so you can study around work."
    steps={courseSteps}
  />
  <WarningCallout>
    Working without an approved permit may attract fines, and you will still
    have to pay an application fee to have the work approved after it is done.
  </WarningCallout>

  <WhyChooseList
    heading="What will you learn?"
    answer="An owner builder takes on the head contractor role, so the course focuses on the knowledge you need to run a residential build lawfully and safely. You finish knowing how the approval process works and where your responsibilities begin and end."
    items={learningOutcomes}
  />

  <ComparisonTable
    heading="What can an owner builder do, and what is off limits?"
    answer="An owner builder permit lets you manage and carry out a wide range of residential work on your own land. It does not cover specialist trades or larger commercial projects. The table below sets out what you can do, and what still needs a licensed contractor."
    rowHeader="Work area"
    columns={['You can', 'You cannot without a licence']}
    rows={scopeRows}
    caption="Work scope verified against QBCC on 22 May 2026. Some specialist work needs a licensed contractor regardless of your permit."
  />

  <AnswerCapsuleSection
    heading="Who can apply for an owner builder permit?"
    answer="To apply for a QBCC owner builder permit you must be an owner named on the property title, a director of the company that owns the land, or a lease occupier who has the owner's written permission. Building experience on its own does not qualify you."
    body="The person who completes the course becomes the Nominated Permit Holder on the application. If the property is owned in joint names, only one owner needs to complete the course and hold the permit. Check that the name on your course certificate matches the name you list on the QBCC permit form, since the regulator cross-checks the two before it issues a permit."
  >
    <WarningCallout label="Eligibility">
      You cannot apply if you, or any applicant on the form, have an unpaid QBCC
      infringement fine, have been served a notice for Tier 1 defective work,
      have had an owner builder permit cancelled in the last 3 years, or already
      hold an owner builder permit issued in the last 6 years. QBCC can grant
      exemptions to the 6-year rule in some cases.
    </WarningCallout>
    <LegalCallout>
      A notification of your owner builder permit is recorded on the property
      title for 7 years. If you sell the property within 6 years of completing
      the build, you must tell the buyer in writing.
    </LegalCallout>
    <VerificationNote lastVerified="2026-05-22">
      <a href={QBCC_ABOUT} class="link-dotted" rel="external">QBCC</a>
    </VerificationNote>
  </AnswerCapsuleSection>

  <PricingTable
    heading="How much does the QLD owner builder course cost?"
    rows={pricingRows}
    caption="QBCC permit application fee verified against QBCC on 22 May 2026. QBCC fees are reviewed on 1 July each year, so confirm the current fee before you apply. The ABE course price is being finalised."
  />
  <LegalCallout>
    The ABE course fee and the QBCC permit application fee are separate. The
    permit application fee is set and collected by QBCC, not by ABE. Course fees
    are reviewed periodically.
  </LegalCallout>

  <FAQSection heading="QLD owner builder course FAQs" items={faqs} />

  <WhyChooseList
    heading="Why choose ABE Education for your owner builder course?"
    answer="ABE Education has delivered owner builder and CPD training to more than 31,000 students across five Australian states and territories since 2007. Courses are written by a licensed builder and independently checked for currency, so what you study reflects current Queensland rules."
    items={whyItems}
  />

  <AnswerCapsuleSection
    heading="How is the course content developed and reviewed?"
    anchorId="content-review"
    answer="ABE uses a two-stage quality process. The course is developed by a licensed builder, then the published page is independently checked for compliance and currency against current Queensland legislation and QBCC requirements. The two stages keep the course accurate and the page trustworthy."
    body="Stage one is course development by an industry expert who verifies the content against the National Construction Code and Queensland building rules. Stage two is an independent compliance and currency review that confirms the legislative references, regulator details, and permit requirements on this page are accurate and up to date. Each stage is carried out by a named expert, not an anonymous team."
  >
    <ExpertReviewerCard
      name="Dominic Ogburn"
      profileHref="/experts/dominic-ogburn"
      role="Course Developer, CEO of ABE Education"
      specialties={['Licensed NSW Builder 369417C', '2005 NSW Fair Trading Award', '40+ Years Experience', '5 Australian Jurisdictions']}
      bio="Forty-plus years in Australian residential construction, beginning at Stuart Brothers Pty Ltd (Sydney builders since 1886). Co-author of Your Home: Buying, Selling, Renovating, Building (Allen and Unwin, 2004). Cited in NSW Legislative Council Hansard (2001) and six Sydney Morning Herald articles. As CEO of ABE Education, Dominic has developed owner builder and CPD training completed by 31,000+ students across five jurisdictions."
      reviewNote="Course content developed by Dominic Ogburn, ABE Education."
    />
    <ExpertReviewerCard
      name="Warwick Smith"
      profileHref="/experts/warwick-smith"
      role="Compliance and Currency Reviewer, Corporate Development Resource Group"
      specialties={['27+ Years in VET', 'Senior Consultant', 'Corporate Development Resource Group']}
      bio="Senior Consultant, Compliance and Operations at Corporate Development Resource Group, with over 27 years across the Australian vocational education and training sector. Former CEO of Training Aid Australia and the Australian Institute of Compliance Professionals. Compliance Manager at TasCollege. Specialist areas include construction, compliance, and operational design."
      reviewNote="Independently reviews ABE's published course pages for legislative currency and regulatory accuracy."
    />
  </AnswerCapsuleSection>
</CoursePageLayout>
